div><span></span></div><div>My absolute Favourite to watch. In my experience, sweetheart dances are rare. The choreography! The matching regalia! When I was younger, I was always drawn to the songs, the dances, the regalia. But my parents were badly affected by the residential schools they went to, so we all missed out on this aspect of our culture. They rediscovered their spirituality in their later years. We do ceremonies, but we don't dance. I'm actually quite a good leather worker and traditional beadworker; I could very well make my own regalia. However, I'm SUPER busy at work (IT specialist) and actually in school part time (for financial management). 

Some day, I will dance.

